Class FoodItem

  • java.lang.Object
    • FoodItem
  • Direct Known Subclasses:

    public class FoodItem
extends java.lang.Object
    The purpose of this class is to declare all the methods that will be called by the child classes as well as extra methods that check item codes and update quantity in stock as well.

      • addItem

        public boolean addItem(java.util.Scanner scan)
        This method creates two patterns to match to when the user inputs the values for the items they are adding It prompts the user for input and then checks the condition of a while loop of the pattern desired. If the pattern is not matched, it prints an error to the user then prompts them again to enter the same value All inputs are taken in as strings and then parsed into the correct data type.
        Parameters:
        scan - Scanner to take in user input
        Returns:
        boolean will return true no matter what because of Patterns to make sure user input is correct and therefore can never fail

      • updateItem

        public boolean updateItem(int amount)
        This method will take in the quantity of items that will be bought or sold and checks if the itemQuantityInStock will still be above 0 or not When the method is called and the parameter is entered, the user input is entered as a negative and therefore only 1 calculation is necessary for both selling and buying
        Parameters:
        amount - the amount the itemQuantityInStock will be modified by.
        Returns:
        returns if the selling or buying was successful or not
